Twister was 113 minutes long with a $92 million budget, and it was released in 1996. By seeing the trailer, and reading that it's shorter and cheaper than Twister, even in 2014, it doesn't seem very exciting.

text: Saw the trailer.  Not going to give them the time of day.  This is hollywood at its worst.  (If that threshold is even possible, given so many many candidates).   Not only is this a complete embarrassment to film as we know it (even though the special effects are state of the art)...it is a complete INSULT to Mother Nature herself.   Nature don't act that way.   She (Mother Nature) is WAAAY more interesting...and frightening, and realistic than the complete bullshit "5 tornado" (not multi-vortex) scenario pictured in this "film." What a laugh!! Hopefully, and EF-6 (doesn't exist but you get my exaggeration) tornado forms and gobbles up all copies and historical existence of this blatant sacrilege to both man and film and nature.   My message  to the Into The Storm creators and profiteers:  Go copulate yourself with a REAL twister...and see if you emerge standing at all.  Have you NO SHAME to leave this piece of cinematic tripe, not only to the world, but as your legacy to your kids and grandkids?  Warner Brothers used to be cool...Bugs Bunny etc.  I remember when.   Now they are just a bunch of inbred morons who have no problem producing sewage and calling it "cinema" and then selling it at the box office.

text: OK, Who do I complain about this worthless piece of crap to?! Gosh this was awful! No plot!!! Heck I knew from the start who was going to get killed. I just picked them out. SURPRISE! They're dead. smh. Terrible! What Nimrod is going to stand there and look at the Tornado headed straight for them and scream, "Oh GOD!" You got that right now get out the way stupid! It's not like the Tornado is going to see you and suddenly move because you are in the way. It's a force of nature. The only thing you can do is get out of it's way. And if I hear the name, 'Tre' again, it will be too soon. :( My favorite tornado was the first one that casually came down the street. Then some idiot was outside the car saying, "I gotta get this shot." He got it all right along with his 3 friends. smh Anyone and I mean 'anyone' that have been in close proximity of an actual tornado knows that it's 100+ times worse then this crap.
